1
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:06,000
(Wedding special)
Our dance king.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:06,900
(Coming up)

3
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:07,540
(This side is ready)

4
00:00:08,980 --> 00:00:09,700
(Ready anytime)

5
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:10,380
(Fully charged)

6
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:11,400
Come on, conga line.

7
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:12,100
(Fully into it)

8
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:13,120
You're that happy?

9
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:16,000
(Dance time)
The wedding march.

10
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,500
(Here comes the built-in soundtrack)

11
00:00:19,540 --> 00:00:23,220
(Old-school artists insisting
on live vocals)

12
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,640
(Easy peasy)
No big deal.

13
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:25,640
(We're all family here)
Say it.

14
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:26,520
(The accent has fully kicked in)
Say it.

15
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,120
I look like the boss, right?

16
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:29,400
(They're all employees)
They're all my employees.

17
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,000
(Loose fit)
I'm dressed like this,

18
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,000
and you want silhouettes?

19
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,470
(Bro gets it)
Just hold her waist like this.

20
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:33,560
(Little bro gets it too)
To show the waist, right?

21
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:34,120
The waist is here.

22
00:00:34,140 --> 00:00:35,300
(Literally legs for days)

23
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:36,100
(Behind the mechanical poster shoot)

24
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:36,980
(Getting into character)

25
00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:38,420
(Serious, polished, proper, icy)

26
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:39,560
(Grade-school fight)
I want it too.

27
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:41,940
(Wen is still the steady one)

28
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:42,240
Go.

29
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,400
Get up. You can't catch up.

30
00:00:43,420 --> 00:00:43,900
(Every word hurts)

31
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,160
What were we aiming at again?

32
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,840
(Still thinking about it)
Shoot the pig's butt.

33
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:47,960
(Little bro takes orders)
Can it reset?

34
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:48,800
(Big sis has an idea)
Use it.

35
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:49,640
(Big bro is battle-ready)
Try it.

36
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:50,600
(Little bro in full command)
Just make it reset.

37
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,600
(Let the games begin)
Wanna play?

38
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,880
They're in the control room now.

39
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:53,820
(What do we do?)

40
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:54,580
(Didn't see that coming)

41
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,800
(Expectant)
Give me a world-shattering high note.

42
00:00:57,820 --> 00:00:59,380
(The village's last hope)

43
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:00,180
(I'm not ready yet)

44
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:04,580
(High-note showdown)

45
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:05,540
(Totally shocked)

46
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:06,940
(Volume up)

47
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:09,200
(Changing tactics)
Little Bunny, be good.

48
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:09,840
The door...

49
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,180
(Open it)

50
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:12,520
(Volume up)
Open it for me!

51
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:16,960
(Volume up)
Open!

52
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,060
=Truth Clubhouse=

53
00:01:22,180 --> 00:01:25,060
(Since we're here,
let's not kill the vibe)

54
00:01:26,660 --> 00:01:27,820
(Settling into the villa)

55
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:29,240
What are we doing here?

56
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:41,460
(Peeking out)

57
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:44,180
(Curious)
There's a show to watch.

58
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:45,780
(One beat late)

59
00:01:46,620 --> 00:01:47,580
(Wrong move)

60
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,040
That was clearly wrong.

61
00:01:49,220 --> 00:01:50,460
(No detail escapes his eyes)

62
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,080
Are you, like, a dance teacher?

63
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,040
(Is this your side hustle?)
You're on.

64
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:53,400
Go.

65
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:53,760
Interact.

66
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:54,920
Go.

67
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:56,680
Our dance king.

68
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:57,680
Get onstage.

69
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,200
Dance.

70
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:00,380
(This side is ready)

71
00:02:00,460 --> 00:02:02,100
(Vibing solo)

72
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,820
(Fully charged)

73
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:05,620
(Ready to go)

74
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:07,580
(Ready anytime)

75
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:08,860
(Learning the dance)

76
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:11,100
(Picked it up fast)

77
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:12,300
(Insane dance skills)

78
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:15,620
(Joy on cheat mode)

79
00:02:16,180 --> 00:02:17,220
(Loving it)

80
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:20,580
(Sneaking a look)

81
00:02:20,820 --> 00:02:23,180
(So sneaky)

82
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:26,020
(Turning it up)

83
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:31,060
(Ning-style sway)

84
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:31,600
Come on.

85
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,240
Wen, hurry.

86
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,240
Dance school girl, go!

87
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,440
(Politely declined)
No, I can't!

88
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,240
Come on. You have to do a solo.

89
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:37,820
(Dandong dance king)

90
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:46,620
(Busy doing absolutely nothing)

91
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,840
Come on, conga line.

92
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,840
Conga line.

93
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:51,560
Hands on shoulders.

94
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,360
Conga line.

95
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,080
Okay.

96
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:57,920
You're that happy?

97
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,560
For no reason?

98
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:01,420
(But his body is into it)

99
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:03,800
Where are you going?

100
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:04,780
(Just dance first)
Link arms.

101
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:06,740
(Letting loose)

102
00:03:07,220 --> 00:03:08,620
(Fully into it)

103
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,200
It's not over yet?

104
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:11,860
(Grandma Jin is tired)

105
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:13,540
(Still has energy)

106
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:16,620
(Yeah, right)

107
00:03:16,660 --> 00:03:18,620
(Still full of energy over here)

108
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:20,780
(Dance time)

109
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,920
There's even an ending pose.

110
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:29,420
(I know this one)

111
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:30,860
(Perfect expression)

112
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:34,160
Okay, stop the music!

113
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,320
All dancers,

114
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,480
go take a break.

115
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,040
Are you two...

116
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,340
(One of the most in-sync thief duos)
The Sync Bandits?

117
00:03:39,580 --> 00:03:40,160
(We've been busted)

118
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,440
This is my other side gig.

119
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,200
Another side gig.

120
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:43,800
Okay.

121
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:45,280
Alright, guests.

122
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,600
Please wait right here.

123
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,360
Just a moment.

124
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,000
Guests?

125
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,880
Isn't this our place?

126
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:49,880
(Bold move)
How did we become guests?

127
00:03:51,020 --> 00:03:52,740
(Whatever. Just act like it's home.)

128
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:55,260
(Very self-motivated)

129
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:56,600
Everyone,

130
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,400
I'm so sorry.

131
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,520
Sorry to interrupt.

132
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,760
(Accent's rubbing off)
Sorry about that.

133
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:00,500
(Accent's contagious)
Sorry.

134
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,400
Looks like you're all locals.

135
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,360
(We're locals)
Yep.

136
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,080
Yep.

137
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,760
Something very urgent has come up.

138
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,640
(We're all our own people)
Say it.

139
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:08,640
Say it.

140
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:10,200
Did you all have this accent

141
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:10,680
before?

142
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,280
Yeah. Always have been.

143
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,160
Couldn't be more local now.

144
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:15,460
(Can't get a word in)

145
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,829
It's fine. Go ahead.

146
00:04:16,829 --> 00:04:17,560
(The four sitting on the floor)
Don't mind them. Go on.

147
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,440
Don't mind them?

148
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,660
(I'm the boss here)
They're not important.

149
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,240
I clearly look like the boss,

150
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:21,760
right?

151
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,920
(They're all employees)
They're all my staff.

152
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,320
Then we'll all listen to you.

153
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:25,720
(I call the shots)
Sure. No problem.

154
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,600
I guess those two chairs
are for the detectives.

155
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:30,600
We moved them over ourselves.

156
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,080
(You choose your own identity outside)
We're the detectives.

157
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:32,440
No.

158
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,440
Everyone, take a look.

159
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,160
(Rehearsing someone else's wedding)
Here are your outfits.

160
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:40,040
Can you actually fit into this?

161
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,400
Let's bring it up first and think later.

162
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,800
(You'll purp-sure fit)
If not, pull it over your head.

163
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,720
Okay. I'll wait for you here.

164
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:49,640
The length is actually just right.

165
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,440
(Accent on point)
This color will purp-sure work.

166
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,840
(Daily teasing the little bro)
Come on. Ding goes first.

167
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:56,000
I'll go. It's fine.

168
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,280
What's there to be scared of?

169
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:57,920
(Leave it to me)
I got this.

170
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,640
Men over here.

171
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,160
One gentleman.

172
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,720
Ladies over here.

173
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:04,300
(Changing)

174
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:05,980
Oh my god. We're really wearing this?

175
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:07,140
So cool.

176
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:09,260
This is kind of cool.

177
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:12,020
(Wants the same fit)
Get me one too. I'll wear red.

178
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,620
Oh my god.

179
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:15,100
You look so handsome.

180
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,900
Come on. Together.

181
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,260
Let's take a selfie.

182
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:21,660
Wow. Heehee.

183
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:24,860
Where's my bride?

184
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,820
Who's my bride?

185
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:29,260
Maybe it's someone wearing a mask.

186
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:31,380
Don't scare me.

187
00:05:31,380 --> 00:05:32,300
Keyu.

188
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:32,860
(Calling from afar)
Yeah?

189
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:34,660
Is that NPC your friend?

190
00:05:34,660 --> 00:05:35,820
Yeah. We filmed together.

191
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:38,220
Yesterday, when he was Uncle Er,
I didn't even recognize him.

192
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,780
(Expert mishearing)
That friend is your uncle?

193
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:41,340
No, he's my brother.

194
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:42,980
So your brother played your uncle?

195
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:44,340
What are you even saying?

196
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:45,420
Have you seen Ning?

197
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:46,460
He's already dressed up.

198
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:47,300
Let's go, bridesmaid.

199
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,260
Let's go, Purple.

200
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,340
(All changed)

201
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:51,180
(Making a grand entrance)

202
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,400
Those sunglasses are doing

203
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,080
nothing.

204
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,600
(Retro vibe)
I'm just trying to stop the audience

205
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,280
from recognizing me.

206
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:57,520
No.

207
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,280
But you look cool. Really cool.

208
00:05:59,280 --> 00:05:59,600
Okay.

209
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:00,840
Guys,

210
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,560
I was just sitting there

211
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,760
and suddenly thought of something.

212
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,280
Go on.

213
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:03,720
What?

214
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,640
Why are we so obedient?

215
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,280
Because we don't ruin the fun.

216
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:09,400
It's because we need to find the truth.

217
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,680
Okay, groomsmen and bridesmaids.

218
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,880
Come over here.

219
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:13,480
Here.

220
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,960
Let's stand in a small V shape.

221
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,820
(Lining up)
That way, it'll be easier

222
00:06:16,820 --> 00:06:17,520
when the bride comes in.

223
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:18,800
Okay.

224
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,600
How does the wedding march go?

225
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:22,280
(Groomsman live backing vocals)

226
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,160
That's the Western one.

227
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,880
You don't actually need to sing it.

228
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,720
We've got music.

229
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:34,460
(Old-school artists insisting
on live vocals)

230
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,200
Okay, that's enough.

231
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,520
Later, we'll give the bride

232
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,600
a little surprise, okay?

233
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,600
Okay.

234
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,280
No problem.

235
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:41,600
Then,

236
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,280
while you sing the wedding march,

237
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:45,200
our little flower kids will...

238
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,400
Wait. The flower kids aren't here yet.

239
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,160
I'm freaking out.

240
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,280
Butler, hurry up!

241
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,440
Where are the flower kids?

242
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,360
The butler is here too?

243
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:52,800
Let me see the butler.

244
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,920
What did he look like in 1996?

245
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,160
(Super curious)
Let's see if it's still him.

246
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,880
Coming!

247
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:03,420
(Butler has logged in)

248
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:05,720
Ms. Wen.

249
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,720
(An Xiaowen instantly
switches to a cutesy voice)

250
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:07,720
Xiaowen!

251
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,840
(Can't hide the smile)

252
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:10,360
(Cute babies)
Mr. He.

253
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,120
Hello.

254
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,040
Mr. Ding.

255
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,720
Hello, Mr. Ding.

256
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,500
Hello.

257
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,060
(Ning starts thinking)

258
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:21,480
If I met my younger self,

259
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,600
what would I say to him?

260
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,480
What would you say?

261
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,280
I'd tell him,

262
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,160
you're gonna be amazing.

263
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,400
You'll become a big star.

264
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:30,960
You'll be a big star.

265
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:33,080
You'll be loved by so many people.

266
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,840
(Just stick with one thing)
So keep trusting what you believe in.

267
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,040
(Time will give you the answer)
Keep loving what you love.

268
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,440
(That hit us right in the feels)
That's kind of touching.

269
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,480
That's kind of touching.

270
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:45,800
What were you doing in your early 20s?

271
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,160
Pulling all-nighters at internet cafes.

272
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:50,100
(Shocking answer)

273
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,680
(Didn't see that coming)
All-night cafe bro, what happened?

274
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,420
(All-night cafe bro is embarrassed)

275
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:54,840
Hurry.

276
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,520
What would you say to your younger self?

277
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,280
I'd say the same thing.

278
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:58,840
You're amazing.

279
