That's true.

837
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:19,920
We didn't know.

838
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:20,760
It's because you came in early.

839
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:21,440
If you'd told me,

840
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:22,840
we would've protected you
with our lives.

841
00:24:22,980 --> 00:24:24,340
(Tell bro first next time)

842
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:27,400
That little gum of yours
really went straight to the heart.

843
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,560
(Taking care of Wen is my duty)

844
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:29,400
No, you're seriously too young.

845
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,400
I'm telling you, out of us guys,

846
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,800
Ning is the most reliable.

847
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:34,320
He only gives you
a shove at the key moment.

848
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:36,000
The rest of the time, he'll catch you.

849
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:39,500
(Reliable? That's Ning)

850
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:40,640
I'm telling you,

851
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:42,200
Zhang Linghe reads people really well.

852
00:24:42,220 --> 00:24:43,240
(Hit Ning right in the heart)

853
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,000
He really does.

854
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:45,840
Ning doesn't lie.

855
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:46,880
Yeah, that's true.

856
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:49,760
Once we're changed, let's get started.

857
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:50,720
(Switching to work mode)
Let's get to work.

858
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:51,440
(Looking around)

859
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:53,880
Your outfits don't really look
like cleaners or...

860
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,480
What are you?

861
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:57,920
(Exclusive He bodyguard online)
I'm a bodyguard. So what?

862
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,320
You're a bodyguard,
but you don't even wear a badge.

863
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:03,680
I'm a personal bodyguard.

864
00:25:03,820 --> 00:25:05,000
(Is that so?)

865
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:05,720
Ning, open the scene.

866
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:06,800
Like, three, two, one.

867
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,040
Make it feel like we suddenly jumped in.

868
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:08,520
Okay, let's go.

869
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:11,260
(Pretending they just teleported in)

870
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:13,040
You're housekeeping?

871
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:13,840
I'm housekeeping.

872
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:14,400
It's the uniform.

873
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,280
(Sudden self-intro)
I'm housekeeping.

874
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,080
I'm security.

875
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:19,120
What are you?

876
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:21,080
I'm a personal bodyguard.

877
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,680
I'm the housekeeping supervisor.

878
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:24,480
(The worker squad assembles)

879
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:25,080
Bodyguard.

880
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,360
Alright, come on.

881
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:28,800
Personal bodyguard.

882
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,160
(Today's role: escort bodyguard)
Personal bodyguards don't push carts.

883
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:31,360
Okay, let's go.

884
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:31,920
Let's go.

885
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:35,300
(Please lower your volume for this part)

886
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:37,940
(An Xiaoding area, An Ke area)

887
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:43,360
There's something
really interesting here.

888
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:45,280
It says only my owner

889
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,180
can open me by hitting a high note.

890
00:25:46,180 --> 00:25:48,540
(Let's see what's going on)

891
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:49,480
Come on, Ning.

892
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:50,540
(Sure it's Ning)

893
00:25:50,580 --> 00:25:51,820
(Excited)

894
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:52,940
(Backing away)
Listen.

895
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,160
This kind of thing says only my owner,

896
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,960
but we don't know who the owner is.

897
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:59,040
So from start to finish,

898
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,520
everyone has to hit a high note.

899
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:02,580
(Enjoying the show)

900
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,920
(Totally agrees)
Everyone? Sure. Fine.

901
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:06,800
It's placed between you two,

902
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,480
so you two probably
have a better chance.

903
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:09,640
You two try first.

904
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,860
(Start your performance)
You two try first.

905
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,600
Exactly.

906
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,880
One of you two, go for it.

907
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:15,980
(Me?)

908
00:26:16,060 --> 00:26:18,420
(Nervously fidgeting with the script)

909
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:19,960
Come on, you try first.

910
00:26:21,780 --> 00:26:22,940
(Volume up)

911
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:25,260
(Volume up)

912
00:26:26,340 --> 00:26:28,020
(Ke's big voice)

913
00:26:28,620 --> 00:26:29,980
(Not bad, little bro)

914
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:32,160
That's my highest.

915
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:33,220
(No response)

916
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:34,160
Was that high enough?

917
00:26:34,620 --> 00:26:35,260
(Volume up)

918
00:26:36,820 --> 00:26:37,460
(Volume up)

919
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:40,040
I think you should sing a line, okay?

920
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:42,440
Give me a world-shattering high note.

921
00:26:42,620 --> 00:26:45,180
(Waiting for the big moment)

922
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:48,040
(Volume up)
Qinghai-Tibet Platea...

923
00:26:48,060 --> 00:26:50,180
(Ke, you did great)

924
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:51,440
Not high enough.

925
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:53,200
Did it open?

926
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:53,800
No.

927
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:54,880
No? Then it's your turn.

928
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:55,760
Your turn.

929
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:02,020
(I'm not ready yet)

930
00:27:05,900 --> 00:27:10,700
(Volume up)

931
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:15,580
(Shocked face)

932
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:15,960
Did it open?

933
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:16,840
That was already really high.

934
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:18,680
Still not open?

935
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:24,880
(Volume up)
Open for me!

936
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:25,760
(Volume up)
Open!

937
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,320
It's Ning then.

938
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,180
(Excited)

939
00:27:29,220 --> 00:27:30,780
(The village's last hope)

940
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:31,440
Ning.

941
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,640
(Waiting for Ning to carry us)
We're not skilled enough yet.

942
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:35,360
My voice

943
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:37,700
(Voice acting up)
has gone hoarse these two days.

944
00:27:38,220 --> 00:27:39,280
(Poor Ning)
It's already half gone.

945
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:40,640
Come on.

946
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:43,880
(Warming up)
Open up!

947
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:46,160
It won't open.

948
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,480
(Volume up)
Open up!

949
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:50,720
(Volume up)
Open!

950
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:51,760
(Still trying)
Open up!

951
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:53,080
Open!

952
00:27:54,100 --> 00:27:56,900
(Not moving at all)

953
00:27:57,120 --> 00:27:57,840
You. Go on.

954
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:58,720
Open!

955
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,340
(Instant singing)

956
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:00,520
Open!

957
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:01,680
No use.

958
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,360
Your turn.

959
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:03,640
I'm the detective.

960
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,240
Exactly.

961
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,440
(No need for the detective to act)
And we still have our box.

962
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,600
Let's do it together. What if it works?

963
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:09,080
Maybe.

964
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:09,440
Okay.

965
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,880
Three, two, one.

966
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:15,020
(Volume up)

967
00:28:15,060 --> 00:28:17,860
(No response)

968
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:22,680
Do we need a vocal run?

969
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:23,820
(Vocal run)

970
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:26,400
Maybe it wants us

971
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:27,720
(Sounds very logical)
to sing a song.

972
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:30,880
Just yelling doesn't
create a good TV moment.

973
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:34,720
(Changing tactics)
Little Bunny, be good. Open

974
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:35,720
the door!

975
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,800
Hurry up.

976
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:37,720
Open up!

977
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:38,700
(Open up)

978
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:39,680
It didn't open.

979
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,300
(Failed)

980
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:42,880
Was the melody wrong?

981
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:43,560
An Ke.

982
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:44,640
Yeah. Try another song.

983
00:28:45,380 --> 00:28:49,140
(Brain overheating)

984
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:51,320
My door is always open.

985
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,000
No. How does our song go again?

986
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,440
Let's start deducing.

987
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:01,680
Unlock the mystery, turn the question,

988
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,640
let's begin tonight!

989
00:29:03,900 --> 00:29:06,140
(No response)

990
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:07,520
Even rock won't open it.

991
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:08,120
My turn.

992
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:08,940
(Time for my show)

993
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:13,920
Under the bridge by the door,
a flock of ducks swims by!

994
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,000
Ducks!

995
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:17,580
(Not giving up)

996
00:29:20,220 --> 00:29:21,060
(An Xiaoning's voice recognized)

997
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:26,680
It's yours.

998
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:28,680
(Ning's box)
The owner is Ning.

999
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:32,080
(So it's yours)
Xiaoning.

1000
00:29:32,780 --> 00:29:35,740
(Mirror surprises keep coming)

1001
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:37,460
(Found glass shards all over the floor)

1002
00:29:39,220 --> 00:29:40,980
(Thinking)

1003
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:45,000
Can we restore

1004
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,340
(A brilliant idea)
these pieces?

1005
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:48,440
Restore it to...

1006
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,380
(Already used)
You've already used the Restore Card.

1007
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:53,920
I think under these shards,

1008
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,240
there might be some clue.

1009
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:57,120
Ding, don't you have...

1010
00:29:57,120 --> 00:29:58,560
Don't you have a Restore Card?

1011
00:29:58,560 --> 00:29:59,160
You used it.

1012
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,220
(Right)
Copy.

1013
00:30:01,320 --> 00:30:02,260
(Bro gets things started)
Use your Copy Card

1014
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:02,680
to copy a Restore Card.

1015
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:04,160
Then restore the mirror.

1016
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:05,680
Right.

1017
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,300
(Sis follows instantly)

1018
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:08,300
(Can't hide those little schemes)

1019
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:09,980
(You guys are something)

1020
00:30:10,060 --> 00:30:11,980
(Troublemaking trio)

1021
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:13,640
(Little bro taking orders)
Can it restore it?

1022
00:30:14,620 --> 00:30:16,020
(Sis has ideas)
Are you using it?

1023
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,100
(Bro's ready to fight)
Just try it.

1024
00:30:18,740 --> 00:30:20,220
(Little bro has swagger)
Just make it restore.

1025
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:21,880
Exactly!

1026
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:23,920
We'll force it to restore.

1027
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:25,620
(Makes sense)

1028
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,200
Wanna play with it?

1029
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,070
(Always joins the charge)
Yes.

1030
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:28,960
Just make it restore.

1031
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,520
(Full of confidence)
Then we'll solve the case.

1032
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:33,200
But what's the point of restoring it?

1033
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,160
We're just restoring it for fun.

1034
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:38,880
(Testing the crew on purpose)
We just want to see

1035
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,160
if they prepared for this.

1036
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,240
They're in the control room right now,

1037
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:43,360
like, what do we do?

1038
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:44,080
Didn't see that coming.

1039
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:46,880
You in?

1040
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:47,520
(Ding wants it)

1041
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:48,040
You in?

1042
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:49,200
You in?

1043
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:50,200
You in?

1044
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:51,400
I'm in.

1045
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:52,500
(Ding gets it)

1046
00:30:52,860 --> 00:30:54,060
(I think it'll work)

1047
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:55,880
(Curious face)
Can we copy it?

1048
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:57,880
(Curious +1)
Can we copy it, director?

1049
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,360
Let's see if they answer you.

1050
00:30:59,420 --> 00:31:01,660
(Waiting...)

1051
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:02,920
They're quiet, guys.

1052
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:04,960
They're discussing like crazy.

1053
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:07,160
Do you want to use a Skill Card?

1054
00:31:10,260 --> 00:31:10,900
(Oh, yo)

1055
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:14,220
(Didn't see that coming)

1056
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,160
He's taunting us.

1057
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:16,940
(Openly provoking us)

1058
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:18,400
Wait. Look, here's the thing.

1059
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,040
(Ke has his own logic)
This glass

1060
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:21,440
is broken in this pool of blood.

1061
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,600
So if we restore it after the crime,

1062
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:25,280
the crime scene might disappear.

1063
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:25,680
Get it?

1064
00:31:27,380 --> 00:31:28,740
(That makes sense)

1065
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:31,200
What if copying it doesn't work?

1066
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:33,400
Restore it to before he died.

1067
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:35,840
If it restores him to before he died,

1068
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:36,640
we're done.

1069
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:37,360
That's on us.

1070
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:38,880
(Asking for trouble)
We'd be messing ourselves up.

1071
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:41,000
(Let's leave it for now)
Forget it. Let's investigate first.

1072
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:44,000
(After investigating)
I think

1073
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:45,240
(A new lead appears)
we should use the Restore Card

1074
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:46,480
to restore this mirror.

1075
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,760
Can it really restore it?

1076
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:50,560
I just want to see

1077
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,560
(A little test)
if the crew can pull this off.

1078
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:52,160
Okay?

1079
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:53,150
(Listen to Ning)
Okay.

1080
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:54,960
What's the Restore Card move?

1081
00:31:55,660 --> 00:31:57,820
(Deep in thought)

1082
00:31:57,920 --> 00:32:01,040
Use the Copy Card
to copy the Restore Card.

1083
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:01,780
(Realizes what he's doing and cracks up)

1084
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:03,600
Then use the Restore Card.

1085
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,640
Use the Restore Card.

1086
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,920
(Restore Card: restores a damaged clue)
Restore this glass.

1087
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:08,480
This mirror.

1088
00:32:10,680 --> 00:32:11,200
Mirror.

1089
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:17,200
Okay.

1090
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:18,760
Okay?

1091
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:21,920
Okay?

1092
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,720
(Now he's unhappy they said yes)
I don't trust that okay!

1093
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:26,080
For real?

1094
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,760
Why don't I believe this?

1095
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:30,440
(Openly doubting them)
The shards have to disappear too.

1096
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:32,540
(Doesn't buy it at all)
Are they fixing it in post?

1097
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,600
No, I just want to ask.

1098
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:36,280
Can you

1099
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:37,160
go up to the body

1100
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,480
and say, "Restore this body"?

1101
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:44,840
Bring him back to life.

1102
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,360
If we restore the burned body,

1103
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:49,800
(Smart move)
we'll know who it is.

1104
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:50,560
Exactly.

1105
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,560
Just restore him
to before he got burned.

1106
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:53,760
He doesn't have to be alive.

1107
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:54,920
Then after a while,

1108
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,500
(Good night, Makka Ningka)
the four of us are all lying there.

1109
00:33:02,060 --> 00:33:04,220
